{"questionId":"27667","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the roots of the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>valid attempt to reduce equation to one involving one trigonometric function&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>correct equation&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mo>±</mo></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1A1A0A1A0</strong></em> for candidates who omit the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>±</mo></math> (for tan or cos) and give only <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>.<br>Award <em><strong>M1A1A0A0A0</strong></em> for candidates who omit the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>±</mo></math> (for tan or cos) and give only <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>M1A1A1A1A0</strong></em> for candidates who give both answers in degrees.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>M1A1A1A1A0</strong></em> for candidates who give both correct answers in radians, but who include additional solutions outside the domain.</p>\n<p>Award a maximum of <em><strong>M1A0A0A1A1</strong></em> for correct answers with no working.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27667","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.10a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the roots of the equation fx=0.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Pythagorean identity, double angles","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.8—Solving trig equations"],"memberSectionIds":